{"parentUuid":null,"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A lot of the development of this project depends upon a queue of tasks, and I'd like to be able to go in and test things pretty easily.\n\n## Fixture File for Testing\n\nCan you set up a fixture file in the test directory with a queue file so that I can open SIFT with a fixture file and just get a sense of what it's doing?\n\nI want to be able to:\n\n1. Open SIFT with a fixture file.\n2. See what it's doing using a predefined queue.\n\nAlso, add multiple of every different file type that we currently support to this fixtures queue.\n\n## Dry Mode Flag\n\nThis makes me think that maybe we should have a `--dry-mode` flag that will replace the calls to Claude with some no-op.\n\nMaybe we could print out what it would invoke Claude with if we have dry-mode.\n\nSo:\n\n1. Add a bead for implementing dry-mode.\n2. Start work on just generating a fixtures queue.\n3. Ensure the queue includes multiple instances of every different file type we currently support."}]},"uuid":"8d1e3d8a-3105-4f57-9d2b-f9f9f16b0cbb","timestamp":"2026-02-11T15:30:26.127Z"}
